videos.headline: Vandy caps great drive with rushing TD
videos.description: RB Ralph Webb punches it in from six yards out to put the Commodores on the board first.

videos.headline: Vanderbilt adds to their lead with passing TD
videos.description: Kyle Shurmur connects with Jared Pinkney for the 10-yard score to put Vandy up 14.

videos.headline: Shurmur 2nd TD pass of the day finds Lipscomb
videos.description: Vandy WR Kalija Lipscomb catches a 45-yard bomb from Kyle Shurmur that boosts the Commodore lead to 21.

videos.headline: Shurmur runs it in for another Vandy score
videos.description: QB Kyle Shurmur can do it all.  Already with two passing touchdowns, he adds a rushing touchdown to his day.

videos.headline: Vanderbilt special teams shows off with a blocked punt
videos.description: Vanderbilt utilizes it's strength to bust through the line and block the punt, setting up great field position.

videos.headline: Another drive, another Vandy TD
videos.description: QB Kyle Shurmur is sharing the wealth and finds Trent Sherfield for a 25-yard strike making it 35-0.

videos.headline: Vanderbilt head coach Derek Mason discusses 1st half successes
videos.description: Head coach Derek Mason is pleased with Kyle Shurmur's performance so far, but urges the Commodores to keep fighting.

videos.headline: Vanderbilt defense gets involved with INT
videos.description: Oren Burks comes down with the interception to give the Commodores great field position

videos.headline: Commodores continue to demolish in 2nd half
videos.description: Kyle Shurmur sends it to Jared Pinkney and collects his fourth passing touchdown.

videos.headline: Vanderbilt wins big over Alabama A&M
videos.description: Commodores were firing on all cylinders this afternoon, but have a tough road ahead.

videos.headline: Vanderbilt defense holds Alabama A&M scoreless
videos.description: The Commodores were strong on both offense and defense in the victory over the Bulldogs.

videos.headline: Vanderbilt may be a team to watch in the SEC
videos.description: QB Kyle Shurmur and head coach Derek Mason lead the Commodores to a 2-0 start and the potential to pose a threat in the SEC.
